  "texts": [
    "Traditional methods of generating paraphrases, such as machine back-translation, often lack syntactic variety, generating sentences that are too similar structurally.",
    "PARAAMR addresses this by using AMR to create paraphrases with greater syntactic diversity while maintaining semantic consistency.",
    "In this approach, the AMR for input text is modified by changing the focus.",
    "To change the focus, nodes are randomly selected as the new focus, and the incoming edges for that node are reversed.",
    "The resulting AMR is then passed to an AMR-to-text generation pipeline to produce the paraphrase."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}